name: WAGONOWHEELS
description: I'll be candid, this one was completely inspired by a Canadian cookies called a Wagon Wheels. Between the N & W the brand has placed an old fashioned wagon wheel from the Wild West pioneer days. I saw the amalgamated word you see in the image. WAGONOWHEELS, which when you break the words apart creates three separate words: WAGON/NOW/WHEELS. From these three ridiculously useless words together, we can make the following sentence: NOW ON A WAGON, EELS ON HEELS; GO WEE ON WHEELS. Absolute jibberish, but fun as hell to make. Is this art? You the reader have to decide that. I base all my work within the specific tenets of structure in the English language, just as any artists would use the foundations of traditional art to use their talents for.
